Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown; washy slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 14. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BY 214.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0521)
